1. How to add github user name and password to git command, so that you can use
    "git push":
    a. if the repo has not been cloned yet:
        git clone https://<USERNAME>:<PASSWORD>@github.com/path/to/repo.git
    b. if you have already cloned the repo:
        git remote set-url origin https://<USERNNAME>:<PASSWORD>@github.com/path/to/repo.git

2. DO NOT use plural in your camelCases vars names: e.g. do NOT use startsAt, instead use startAt

3. Make certain node version the default one in Linux and nvm:  nvm alias default 14.5.0

4. nvm install --lts >>> install the latest node